				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree.  We did this one yesterday, and for someone with 535-all resists, we sure got hit a lot.  Lucy says -160 chromatic, and we don't think it's accurate.  FEELS more like -350 chromatic.  The solution is dog-simple, though.  Have your casters and healers take three steps down the ramp when the fight starts, listen for the AE casting sound (like thunder) pop your head up like one of those &quot;whack-a-mole&quot; things at carnivals, cast, and get your hiney back down the ramp.  12 seconds between casts, someone said.  No one got hit with silence that way except the close in melee, and who cares?  They talk too much anyway.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
