				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Torment Fight<a name="67669"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 8:25 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Did Metala today for a giuldy.  Roughly 12-15 people, fairly light on healing (2 druids, 1 cleric main, 1 cleric 2 box), and not a huge amount of tankage (1 warrior) or DPS.  We are a Time+ guild, I had roughly 9500 HP for the event, to give you an idea of what we brought to the fight.
<br />

<br />
Fight lasted a ballpark of 12 minutes, and to quote the tank 'afk - making coffee'...  The hardest part of the fight was when the room repopped, and for that its a case of getting someone to agro mob, drag it behind the wall, and mez it.
<br />

<br />
Have casters stand behind the wall when they can, the AE silence wont hit them - can heal through the wall no problems.  For me, I gave up with songs and just had manasong going, just to make sure the healers didnt go OOM.  My YALP parse said 520k hitpoints, assume 10-15% lost, so probably 600k with regen, DoT's, DS's etc.
<br />

<br />
It was not a hard fight, 2 groups is overkill if you have good gear.  The MT took 90k damage in that 12 minutes, with max being 1150.  Clear the room as fast as you can, make sure you start as soon as possible to maximise the time before repops, and it really is a simple fight.  There were no surprises when the casters were hid.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
