				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Torment Fight<a name="68039"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 25 04 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Did the fight yesterday.  I too went looking everywhere for info on where she is as she is not on bard track from zone in.
<br />

<br />
Sorry I don't have the loc, but I think the directions are pretty simple so you shouldn't need.  Go up from zone in, past ravens, continue straight at the first intersection which will then take you (after a small bit of winding) to Saryrn's Tower.  You should be able to see on bard track from there (a bruised woman - light blue con for 70).  Turn right at the intersection before Saryrn's tower and stay straight.  You go up a long ramp to building.  There she is inside.
<br />

<br />
Clear room, have healers behind convenient wall, and have casters joust AE.  Pretty simple fight so I didn't bother to actually call AE for jousting.
<br />

<br />
There's a couple of small structures in that room making it possible for Metala to get pushed on top (and out of range for loot - can I say flashbacks of CT on house? lol :p).  When Metala gets low, just have tank move out so you can loot np.  I think that's a better option than risk AE hitting healers if Metala isn't basically cornered there.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
